     <div id="hide">
      <h1>Compensation and Benefits</h1>
     </div> 
     <div class="col396 nomargin"> 
      <div class="row entry"> 
       <div class="row feat-content                         "> 
        <div class="promo-caption">
         <div>
          <a href="benefits-of-belonging.html"><img alt="Benefits of Belonging video" height="240" src="../_files/images/video-workingatUC.jpg" width="390"></a> 
          <p>Most UC employees are eligible for benefits, but your benefits package depends on the length of your appointment, how many hours you work, and your appointment type. Retirees are eligible based on their age and years of service credit at retirement. <a href="eligibility/index.html">Learn more about benefits eligibility</a>.</p> 
          <p>If you are represented by a union, your compensation and benefits are governed by <a href="../labor/bargaining-units/index.html">your union’s contract</a>.</p> 
         </div>
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="divider-long"></div> 
      <div class="row entry"> 
       <h2 class="row                                         blue01           cat-title">About Your Benefits</h2> 
       <div class="row promo"> 
        <a class="promo-hdr-level1" href="health-plans/index.html">Health Plans</a> 
        <div class="promo-caption">
         <p>As a UC employee or retiree, you have a choice of medical plans, dental plans and a vision plan for you and your family members. Here you’ll find information about the plans, your costs, enrolling and de-enrolling, links to carriers’ websites and more.</p>
        </div> 
        <ul> 
         <li><a href="health-plans/medical/index.html">Medical Plans</a></li> 
         <li><a href="health-plans/dental/index.html">Dental Plans</a></li> 
         <li><a href="health-plans/vision/index.html">Vision Plan</a></li> 
        </ul> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="divider-short"></div> 
      <div class="row entry"> 
       <div class="row promo"> 
        <a class="promo-hdr-level1 " href="retirement-benefits/index.html">Retirement Benefits</a> 
        <div class="promo-caption">
         <p>UC offers comprehensive retirement benefits including a traditional pension plan, voluntary retirement savings plans and retiree health insurance.</p>
        </div> 
        <ul> 
         <li><a href="retirement-benefits/ucrp/index.html">UC Retirement Plan</a></li> 
         <li><a href="retirement-benefits/ucrs/index.html">Retirement Savings Program</a></li> 
         <li><a href="retirement-benefits/health-welfare/index.html">Retiree Health and Welfare Benefits</a></li> 
         <li><a href="https://ucfocusonyourfuture.mysecurebenefitsportal.com/">Financial education workshops and webinars</a></li> 
        </ul> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="divider-short"></div> 
      <div class="row entry"> 
       <div class="row promo"> 
        <a class="promo-hdr-level1 " href="disability-life-accident/index.html">Disability, Life &amp; Accident Insurance</a> 
        <div class="promo-caption">
         <p>To help you prepare for the unexpected, UC offers insurance plans to provide a financial safety net for you and your family.</p>
        </div> 
        <ul> 
         <li><a href="disability-life-accident/disability/index.html">Short Term and Supplemental Disability</a></li> 
         <li><a href="disability-life-accident/life-insurance/index.html">Life Insurance</a></li> 
         <li><a href="disability-life-accident/add/index.html">Accidental Death &amp; Dismemberment Insurance</a></li> 
        </ul> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="divider-short"></div> 
      <div class="row entry"> 
       <div class="row promo"> 
        <a class="promo-hdr-level1 " href="other-benefits/index.html">Other Benefits</a> 
        <div class="promo-caption">
         Business Travel Accident Insurance
         <br>Flexible Spending Accounts
         <br>Family Care Resources
         <br>Homeowner/Renter/Auto Insurance
         <br>Legal Insurance
         <br>Tuition Discounts 
         <ul> 
         </ul>
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
